            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-248-person2071">
                  ANN 
                  LOUISA ALLEN
               <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2071" type="surname" value="LOUISA ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2071" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2071" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Joseph Allen. I keep a milliner's shop in <placeName id="t18320216-248-crimeloc1410">Norton-falgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320216-248-crimeloc1410" type="placeName" value="Norton-falgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320216-248-crimeloc1410" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-248-off1408 t18320216-248-crimeloc1410"></join>; the prisoner came there on the 17th of January, alone - I was standing in the back parlour; I saw her take up a cap out of the window, and a blue handkerchief - I went into the shop, and when I saw her I knew her very well, and thought it was of no use to speak to her then - she dropped the cap, as I suppose, between herself and the counter; I went into the parlour again, and told my girls to watch - they gave me information; I went out when they said, "Now, Ma'am;" I found her with a cap, which she had taken - he came to buy nothing, but in the same manner as she had come before - she desired me to put a cap by for her, and not to mix it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-248-person2072">
                  CAROLINE 
                  LITTLE
               <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2072" type="surname" value="LITTLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2072" type="given" value="CAROLINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2072" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the parlour - Mrs. Allen came into the parlour and told us to watch, and I saw the prisoner drop the cap; then she stopped down and put something into her bosom.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-248-person2073">
                  HENRY 
                  DEPIES
               <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2073" type="surname" value="DEPIES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2073" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-person2073" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and have the cap, which I saw Mrs. Allen take from her; I heard her say,"You have robbed me, and I know you have the property;" she took this cap from her bosom - she was searched in my presence, and another new cap was found on her, and half a yard of lace; she had a sovereign and three duplicates.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought it about a fortnight before, of a young lady who was in her shop, for half a crown; I am a <rs id="t18320216-248-deflabel1411" type="occupation">mantua-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-248-defend2068 t18320216-248-deflabel1411"></join> - there are plenty of caps like that.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320216-248-verdict1412" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-verdict1412" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 40. - <rs id="t18320216-248-punish1413" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320216-248-punish1413" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-248-defend2068 t18320216-248-punish1413"></join>
